Turkey 's Sikorsky Helicopter Shot down by PKK
ANKARA , November 29 ( Xinhua ) -- The rebels of the outlawed Kurdish Workers ' Party ( PKK ) shot down a Sikorsky helicopter of Turkey , killing 16 soldiers , a Turkish official statement said on Sunday .
The statement issued by the General Staff said that PKK militants shot down the helicopter in Hakkari province bordering northern Iraq at Friday noon .
Sixteen out of the 18 sodliers on board were killed , another one was wounded and the other still missing .
" The helicopter crashed when the pilot was shot in gunfire by terrorists on the ground and he lost control of the helicopter , " the statement said .
The helicopter crashed when it was on a reconnaissance and emergency back-up mission in the region , close to northern Iraq .
In May last year , The PKK guerrillas used Russian-made SAM-7 missiles to shoot down two helicopters during an incursion by Turkish government troops into northern Iraq to wipe out PKK camps there .
The PKK has been fighting a separatist war in southeastern Turkey , which has claimed over 37,000 lives in conflicts since August 1984 .
